Privacy Policy for Neon Vortex

Last updated: January 2026

Neon Vortex is an endless arcade shooter game developed by David Taylor, operating under the name DCT Milk Games (‚Äúwe,‚Äù ‚Äúus,‚Äù or ‚Äúour‚Äù).

Your privacy is important to us. This Privacy Policy explains what information (if any) is collected when you play Neon Vortex, how it is used, and what rights you have ‚Äî including special protections for children.

1. Information We Collect

Neon Vortex is designed to collect little to no personal information.

We do not collect:

Your name, email address, or other personal details

Text input (the game has no text entry)

Account information (there are no accounts)

Device identifiers such as Advertising ID or Android ID

IP address

Location data

Gameplay analytics

Crash logs or diagnostics

2. Advertising

Neon Vortex shows ads to support the game.

Ads are provided through Google advertising services

Ads are configured to be compliant with child-privacy laws

Ads are not personalized

We do not knowingly allow ads that are based on a player‚Äôs personal information

While we do not collect personal data ourselves, Google may process limited information as necessary to display ads. You can learn more about how Google handles data in their own privacy policy.

3. Children‚Äôs Privacy

Neon Vortex is a general-audience game and may be played by children.

We take children‚Äôs privacy seriously:

We do not knowingly collect personal information from children under 13

The game does not include chat, messaging, accounts, or social features

No text input is possible in the game

If you are a parent or guardian and believe your child has provided personal information in connection with Neon Vortex, please contact us and we will take appropriate action.

4. Third-Party Services

Neon Vortex uses:

Google advertising services (for displaying ads)

We do not use:

Analytics services

Social media integrations

External links

User tracking tools

Third-party services are governed by their own privacy policies.

5. Data Security

Because Neon Vortex does not collect or store personal data, there is no personal information stored on our servers. We design the game to minimize data exposure and privacy risk.

6. Your Rights

Depending on your location, you may have rights under privacy laws such as GDPR or similar regulations, including:

The right to know what data is collected

The right to request deletion of personal data

Since we do not collect personal data, most requests can be resolved quickly by confirming that no such data is stored.

7. Changes to This Policy

If Neon Vortex changes in a way that affects privacy (for example, new features or services), this Privacy Policy may be updated. Any changes will apply going forward.

